cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.ST

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method of probabilistic prediction based on conformal prediction, which is a machine learning technique. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as conformal prediction is a type of algorithmic decision-making that is used in AI. Additionally, the paper applies the method to the USPS data set, which is a common benchmark in computer vision, suggesting it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper's focus on prediction and probability also suggests it could belong to cs.ST (Statistics). Finally, the paper's use of machine learning and statistical techniques suggests it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
